    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Go to Settings -> General.\r\n2. From \"Theme\" change the theme to Dark.\r\n3. From \"Language\" select any language other that the \"System default\".\r\n3. Return to the homescreen.\r\n4. Rotate the device to Landscape mode.\r\n5. Observe that the theme changes.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nThe transition is done smoothly, the Dark theme is still displayed.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nRotating the device to Landscape mode when any language other than the \"System default\" is selected, causes the theme to incorrectly change from Dark to \"Light\" - like theme, with the white text color. \r\nThe incorrect theme will continue to be displayed on both Landscape and Portrait mode until the user will navigate to another page/menu.\r\n\r\n### Device information\r\n\r\n*Android device: LG G7 fit (Android 8.1), Lenovo Tab M10 (Android 10), Sony Xperia Z5 Premium (Android 7.1.1).\r\n*Focus version: RC 95.1.0, latest debug build from main 12/02.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89388888/144399891-2f7ad36a-74d0-44e8-91a6-de79d897cf0d.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n",
